{
  "texts": [
    "For example, Dai et al. (2022) use attributions to locate knowledge neurons, modify them, and edit factual knowledge of the NLP model.",
    "The algorithmic perspective underscores interpretability for debugging, refining model deployment, and forecasting progress.",
    "The Business Perspective: focuses on leveraging interpretability across various sectors to enhance informed decision-making, legal compliance, and user trust.",
    "Models often aid decision-making at the business level (e.g., sentiment analysis for market research (Hartmann et al., 2022)) and at the user level (e.g., LLMs assisting physicians in patient diagnostics (Clusmann et al., 2023)).",
    "In both cases, interpretability aids ensure well-grounded and trustworthy decisions (Lai and Tan, 2019)."
  ]
}